Kakamega Senator aspirant Boni Khalwale has for the second time this year congratulated his children for their performance in the just-released 2021 KCSE results. According to the results shared by Boni, Flavia Shimuli Khalwale, a student of Alliance Girls' High School scored a mean grade of A minus." Her twin brother, Steven Kapten Khalwale got a grade C plus. The politician took to Twitter to announce the results and thanked the teachers of Alliance Girls' and Kakamega Boys High school. "Celebrating twin blessings! My family and I thank God together with the teaching and non-teaching staff of Alliance Girls High School and Kakamega High School," he said. In March 2022, Khalwale took to Twitter to share a message of gratitude following her daughter's impressive performance in KCPE 2021 exams. "My family and I, in 1,000 special ways thank God, the teaching and non-teaching staff of Malinya Primary School and Kakamega Hill Junior School for the 402," he tweeted. His daughter, Melissa Khamwenyi Khalalwe had scored 402.